libdvdcss: libdvdcss (DVD access library)
libdvdcss: 
libdvdcss: libdvdcss is a cross-platform library for transparent DVD device
libdvdcss: access with on-the-fly CSS decryption. It currently runs under Linux,
libdvdcss: FreeBSD, NetBSD, OpenBSD, BSD/OS, Solaris, BeOS, Win95/Win98,
libdvdcss: Win2k/WinXP, MacOS X, HP-UX, QNX, and OS/2. It is used by libdvdread
libdvdcss: and most DVD players such as VLC because of its portability and
libdvdcss: because, unlike similar libraries, it does not require your DVD drive
libdvdcss: to be region locked.
libdvdcss: 
